One Pot Pasta with Sausage, Mushrooms, and Peas
  --Cook's Country
  
1 lb cremini mushrooms, trimmed and sliced thin
1 lb sweet italian sausage, casings removed
2 shallots, chopped
1 1/4 tsp salt
1 tsp pepper
1/4 tsp red pepper flakes
1/2 c dry white wine
12 oz (4 1/2 c) medium pasta shells
4 c water
2 c frozen peas
1 c fresh basil leaves, chopped
1 oz parmesan cheese, grated (1/2 c) + extra for serving
2 tsp grated lemon zest + lemon wedges for serving

In large dutch oven set over high heat, cook mushrooms, sausage, shallots, salt, pepper, and pepper flakes, stirring frequently and breaking up meatm until liquid has evaporated and fond has formed on bottom of pot, ~15 min. Add wine and cook, scraping up fond, until liquid has evaporated, ~2 min. Stir in pasta and water and bring to a boil. Reduce heat to medium low, cover, and simmer, stirring occasionally, until pasta is al dente, ~10 min (some liquid will remain in bottom of pot). Off heat, add peas, basil, cheese, and lemon zest. Stir vigorously for 1 min, until sauce has thickened. Serve with extra paremsan and lemon wedges.


Notes: Can sub button mushrooms for cremini, and 12 oz (3 1/2 c) orecchiette for the medium pasta shells. For non-alcoholic version, sub 1/2 c water for wine and stir in 1 tbsp lemon juice with the lemon zest.
